w dimensions to integer; r=automatedtester, a=test-only\n\nThe specification says nothing about coercing to integer.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Cq5Wbo2vIAD", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9df0ea5a8f8f9bd4ec35ae4f30afe45ce6b0c396", "parents": ["f63502a8a7ead318b4ba35a413cce395de1da79a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1280101 - Remove check for window sizes larger than screen; r=automatedtester, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: K2l0pPfGbGp", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_set_window_size.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "85ccaed0061c96468658c35137c86467166624d5", "parents": ["9df0ea5a8f8f9bd4ec35ae4f30afe45ce6b0c396"], "tags": []}], "date": 1467122358, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6133": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nihanth Subramanya \u003cnhnt11@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1272531 - Make advanced panel in about:neterror stretch to fill content width. r=Gijs, a=gchang", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/aboutNetError.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "39023f2bbf6e44d29165130cd5e19d35385f0b97", "parents": ["85ccaed0061c96468658c35137c86467166624d5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1467125870, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6134": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump. CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "20aee191ee5748a524e0d1ef29213bdd042fb6a8", "parents": ["39023f2bbf6e44d29165130cd5e19d35385f0b97"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 676a32cdd41fd372f4c6df3a4954939f73a6ef02 with FIREFOX_48_0b4_BUILD1, FIREFOX_48_0b4_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cf85e0aa283eaaa522ddbc2749945ea97f249933", "parents": ["20aee191ee5748a524e0d1ef29213bdd042fb6a8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1467136220, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "6135": {"changesets": [{"author": "Wes Kocher \u003cwkocher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 85ccaed0061c (bug 1280101) on the guess that it's putting Windows machines into a bad state a=backout CLOSED TREE", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_set_window_size.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2b22de79c849b6c915b01f0d306699261b2fdee3", "parents": ["cf85e0aa283eaaa522ddbc2749945ea97f249933"], "tags": []}], "date": 1467151132, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kwierso@gmail.com"}, "6136": {"changesets": [{"author": "Neil Deakin \u003cneil@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1276120, hide popups when a parent window is being minimized, handles the case where the window is minimized via a keyboard shortcut, r=jmathies, a=gchang", "files": ["widget/windows/nsWindow.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "432e034161c2eaf28fdc83a5148ec3f1986301fc", "parents": ["2b22de79c849b6c915b01f0d306699261b2fdee3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1467186423, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6137": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrzej Hunt \u003cahunt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1280539 - don't open topsites into reader view if stored as offline reader-view page. r=sebastian, a=gchang\n\nBy default, i.e. for most lists in the homepanels, we want to open the offline reader-view version\nof a page if the page is stored as an offline reader-view bookmark (TwoLinePageRow shows the bookmark\nand offline status for pages, not only in bookmarks, but also in the list of top sites, awesomescreen\nresults, and history). The only exception is the topsites grid, where we don't offer any indication\nof the bookmark or offline status of a page. For now the expectation is that topsites open the\nnormal version of a page, so we need to bypass the usual flow for that case.\n\n(It's possible the UI around this would change in future, but with the current UI this is probably\n the most obvious / least frustrating behaviour.)\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BMpGG4KQ62w", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/BrowserApp.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/home/HomePager.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/home/TopSitesPanel.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2f4351f2cf731b6914aed0df75d72ec1c71d8126", "parents": ["432e034161c2eaf28fdc83a5148ec3f1986301fc"], "tags": []}], "date": 1467212340, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6138": {"changesets": [{"author": "Blake Kaplan \u003cmrbkap@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1274516 - Add a helper to iterate over all ContentParents and use it to clear the image cache in both the parent and child processes. r=billm r=seth, a=gchang", "files": ["dom/ipc/ContentChild.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentChild.h", "dom/ipc/ContentParent.cpp", "dom/ipc/ContentParent.h", "dom/ipc/PContent.ipdl", "image/imgLoader.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "82eb59127df7b326ecec29c9cb462b4671320302", "parents": ["2f4351f2cf731b6914aed0df75d72ec1c71d8126"], "tags": []}], "date": 1467212490, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6139": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andy McKay \u003camckay@mozilla.com", "branch": "default", "desc": "bug 1282568 sign add-ons in browser_update tests r=aswan a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6kF005zOosv", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/addons/browser_update1_1.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser/addons/browser_update1_2.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/browser