 "browser/themes/osx/browser.css", "browser/themes/osx/tabbrowser/tab-selected-end-yosemite-inactive.svg", "browser/themes/osx/tabbrowser/tab-selected-start-yosemite-inactive.svg", "browser/themes/windows/browser.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ebd3919e8a3a0c4bcc5c3933ab693b44b38f490e", "parents": ["8e54a7dccda8dfa6d61f45d4804de5c95a205fb7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468182554, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "dgottwald@mozilla.com"}, "6195": {"changesets": [{"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1270753 part 1 - Use the weak reference itself as an index for OldWindowSize item. r=smaug, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3X7O5pAuZ3N", "files": ["dom/base/nsDOMWindowUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fb263c395e159da792d520aa7ff84a3da92457ef", "parents": ["ebd3919e8a3a0c4bcc5c3933ab693b44b38f490e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Xidorn Quan \u003cme@upsuper.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1270753 part 2 - Clean up corresponding old window size when the DOMWindowUtils is destroyed. r=smaug, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3l3jeP4NWZ3", "files": ["dom/base/nsDOMWindowUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa7a42657c48de78ba1a0fefd43d1c6ed233e97a", "parents": ["fb263c395e159da792d520aa7ff84a3da92457ef"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468192485, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "xquan@mozilla.com"}, "6196": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nils Ohlmeier [:drno] \u003cdrno@ohlmeier.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285318: turn of WebRTC TCP packet filtering. r=mjf a=lizzard\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7kmAJlscG9a", "files": ["media/mtransport/nr_socket_prsock.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d9400e38d2d11b4faa0c085491dbf815540ef86f", "parents": ["fa7a42657c48de78ba1a0fefd43d1c6ed233e97a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468209323, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "rjesup@wgate.com"}, "6197": {"changesets": [{"author": "Alexander Surkov \u003csurkov.alexander@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1279665 - skip aria-owns deferred accessible creation for XUL elements. r=yzen, a=gchang", "files": ["accessible/base/TreeWalker.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ca9bac69cffb6c985b5cb9ef0b7acd7f6eb5889e", "parents": ["d9400e38d2d11b4faa0c085491dbf815540ef86f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1276054 - Uplift pocket changes from partner. r=gijs, a=gchang", "files": ["browser/components/uitour/test/browser.ini", "browser/extensions/pocket/content/main.js", "browser/extensions/pocket/content/panels/js/signup.js", "browser/extensions/pocket/content/pktApi.jsm", "browser/extensions/pocket/install.rdf.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f52ccfac4ff0d87e92b903d2762a059fd3200fb4", "parents": ["ca9bac69cffb6c985b5cb9ef0b7acd7f6eb5889e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1272557 - Delay initializing PushService and DLC; r=snorp, a=gchang\n\nDelay initialization of PushService and DLC in GeckoApplication to after\nthe Gecko:Ready message. That way, hopefully they give up some CPU time\nto other initialization tasks.", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoApp.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoApplication.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5c39f5f66157f5e0ab08ba0a549c502f166d4b7e", "parents": ["f52ccfac4ff0d87e92b903d2762a059fd3200fb4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jan Henning \u003cjh+bugzilla@buttercookie.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1242562 - Byte count rounding shouldn't depend on the decimal separator used. r=mak, a=gchang\n\nCurrently, download sizes on Fennec aren't rounded for locales using a \".\" as their decimal separator.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 54sBvTrNAln", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/downloads/DownloadUtils.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "03fad0a46c36c3376fd94532be2deee2d25dcbc3", "parents": ["5c39f5f66157f5e0ab08ba0a549c502f166d4b7e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1280446 - Create PushService if needed; r=snorp, a=gchang\n\nIf PushService has not been created when getInstance is called, create\nthe PushService instead of throwing an error. This fixes a possible race\ncondition between initializing PushService and receiving a push message,\nwhere we can receive a push message first.", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/gcm/GcmInstanceIDListenerService.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/gcm/GcmMessageListenerService.java", "mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/push/PushService.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7403ba7e150841127e9e9a163635f99ccb6527f8", "parents": ["03fad0a46c36c3376fd94532be2deee2d25dcbc3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Randall Barker \u003crbarker@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285239 - Scrolling can randomly get interrupted and show overscroll effect. r=botond, a=gchang", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/AndroidAPZ.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e0770c0fbc7b7bbcb6be3d4d063f3d4a0ffdb7a2", "parents": ["7403ba7e150841127e9e9a163635f99ccb6527f8"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468221857, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6198": {"changesets": [{"author": "Nils Ohlmeier [:drno] \u003cdrno@ohlmeier.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1279146 - Clean up streams on shutdown. r=bwc a=lizzard", "files": ["media/mtransport/nricectx.cpp", "media/mtransport/nricemediastream.cpp", "media/mtransport/transportlayerdtls.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9d734024ed35d74449601cc04917b327e0973c0d", "parents": ["e0770c0fbc7b7bbcb6be3d4d063f3d4a0ffdb7a2"], "tags": ["FIREFOX_48_0b7_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_48_0b7_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1468222033, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6199": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1280446 - Follow-up to fix another possible crash; r=me a=gchang", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/push/PushService.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7c9c052d51bb26ff6bfb2a7eae649b1b7f008e32", "parents": ["9d734024ed35d74449601cc04917b327e0973c0d"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468272615, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "nchen@mozilla.com"}, "6200": {"changesets": [{"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1277123 - Only clear the containing block clip when entering an out of flow with an unknown clip. r=mattwoodrow, a=gchang\n\nThe content clip is still valid, as we are only descending into content descendants.\n\nThe clip for content descendants that the root scroll frame creates so content doesn't overflow (visually or for event handling) the main scrollbar can get cleared otherwise.", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a2bd45d1472047ce1a6a54cde032fbea2e2cddc5", "parents": ["7c9c052d51bb26ff6bfb2a7eae649b1b7f008e32"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1271899 - inspector box-model: add div wrapper to close editors on click;r=gl, a=gchang\n\nThe XUL tabpanel can no longer receive userfocus to avoid scrollbars\nstealing the focus. Editors are using the blur event to destroy\nthemselves, which was no longer working if a user click ended up on\nthe tabpanel element.\n\nAdd a wrapper inside the layout view panel taking\n100% width and height to make sure clicks performed outside of the layout\ncontainer will trigger a blur event on a focused editor.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JmZluQ6LzFl", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/inspector.xul", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser_layout_editablemodel.js", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser_layout_editablemodel_bluronclick.js", "devtools/client/themes/layout.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "60a96ba61e4cc0acfe42e91f96836aed4c7f3d21", "parents": ["a2bd45d1472047ce1a6a54cde032fbea2e2cddc5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ray Lin \u003cralin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1276686 - Prevent selection when tapping on reader mode toolbar. r=margaret, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9A4aZBUTKf6", "files": ["mobile/android/themes/core/aboutReaderControls.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f717e101c78709aa6e5b0c29826c856a20d388b", "parents": ["60a96ba61e4cc0acfe42e91f96836aed4c7f3d21"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468333265, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6201": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1255555 - When a frame reconstruction triggers caret elements to be cloned, ensure the dummy touch listeners are re-registered on the clones. r=tylin a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8txWmd64LC9", "files": ["layout/base/AccessibleCaret.cpp", "layout/base/AccessibleCaret.h", "layout/base/AccessibleCaretEventHub.cpp", "layout/base/AccessibleCaretManager.cpp", "layout/base/AccessibleCaretManager.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1748a233dae02d02e14bb64d378dc8cc3ae4a1b0", "parents": ["0f717e101c78709aa6e5b0c29826c856a20d388b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468347550, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kgupta@mozilla.com"}, "6202": {"changesets": [{"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Automatic version bump. CLOSED TREE NO BUG a=release", "files": ["browser/config/version_display.txt"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a8789ffd17ce835528e73c23691aa7cbf6e0f870", "parents": ["1748a233dae02d02e14bb64d378dc8cc3ae4a1b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld \u003crelease@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug - Tagging 9d734024ed35d74449601cc04917b327e0973c0d with FIREFOX_48_0b7_BUILD1, FIREFOX_48_0b7_RELEASE a=release CLOSED TREE", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6cf4ff99bea9b7dc6f3c291778917c8daae2b49a", "parents": ["a8789ffd17ce835528e73c23691aa7cbf6e0f870"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468351381, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "6203": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jorg K", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD480b1_2016071201_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 333064 - Fix space insertion in copy of CJK text. r=enndeakin a=jorgk DONTBUILD", "files": ["dom/base/nsCopySupport.cpp", "dom/base/test/mochitest.ini", "dom/base/test/test_bug333064.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9a5abbdc1fb41a32b6883b697290726c8a338dea", "parents": ["6cf4ff99bea9b7dc6f3c291778917c8daae2b49a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jorg K", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD480b1_2016071201_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1274242 - Linkify should not stop at |. r=valentin a=jorgk DONTBUILD", "files": ["netwerk/streamconv/converters/mozTXTToHTMLConv.cpp", "netwerk/test/unit/test_mozTXTToHTMLConv.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f960fa659d35546c73c694de9564b0d2fc1019af", "parents": ["9a5abbdc1fb41a32b6883b697290726c8a338dea"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jorg K", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD480b1_2016071201_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Bug 1274602 - When checking for tags, allow for white-space. r=honzab a=jorgk DONTBUILD", "files": ["netwerk/streamconv/converters/mozTXTToHTMLConv.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "69f8c8df54e4d80a49d9002df379c3eafb80f08c", "parents": ["f960fa659d35546c73c694de9564b0d2fc1019af"], "tags": ["THUNDERBIRD_48_0b1_BUILD3", "THUNDERBIRD_48_0b1_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1468358597, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "mozilla@jorgk.com"}, "6204": {"changesets": [{"author": "Chris Pearce \u003ccpearce@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1282577 - Guard against multiple intr messages causes us to multi-delete GMP actors. r=jesup,a=lizzard\n\nThis is a regression from bug 1162358.\n\nWe must be hitting the #ifndef SHMEM_ALLOC_IN_CHILD block in\nGMPVideoDecoderChild::Alloc() with multiple allocs doing intr calls at once.\nIf this happens when a DecodingComplete() comes in, we'll end up sending one\ntask to re-call RecvDecodingComplete for every Alloc() blocked on an intr\nresponse.  This would result in us ending up trying to Send__delete__() in\nRecvDecodingComplete() twice.  Which causes the runtime abort we're seeing\nhere.\n\nI think that could happen in the WidevineVideoDecoder if a Decode message comes\nin, and goes into a ReturnOutput(), tries to alloc a frame and has to spin on\nan intr message response, and another Decode message comes in and does the\nsame, so GMPVideoDecoderChild::mNeedShmemIntrCount will be 2, and then a\nDecodingComplete comes in, and when two tasks on the stack in\nGMPVideoDecoderChild::Alloc() finish they both end up dispatching a task to\nre-call GMPVideoDecoderChild::RecvDecodingComplete(). So we end up trying to\nSend__delete__() in RecvDecodingComplete() twice.\n\nI expect the same problem exists in the GMPVideoEncoder too.\n\nintr, or spinning event loops in general for that matter, is evil.\n\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AKsvP62G3Cx", "files": ["dom/media/gmp/GMPVideoDecoderChild.cpp", "dom/media/gmp/GMPVideoEncoderChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "01aead8192bd5dca6f1dbef7424da9f0a70bc4a9", "parents": ["6cf4ff99bea9b7dc6f3c291778917c8daae2b49a"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468366771, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cpearce@mozilla.com"}, "6205": {"changesets": [{"author": "tbirdbld", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD480b1_2016071201_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Added THUNDERBIRD_48_0b1_RELEASE THUNDERBIRD_48_0b1_BUILD3 tag(s) for changeset 69f8c8df54e4. DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE a=release", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a69bc356c8c86f2f0b3c25b9b25fb1edcc62f586", "parents": ["69f8c8df54e4d80a49d9002df379c3eafb80f08c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468374060, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "tbirdbld"}, "6206": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1283999 - Rewrite and complement element retrieval tests; r=automatedtester a=test-only\n\nMany tests for the plural Find Element, Find Element From Element,\nand FInd Elements From Element commands were missing.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DFGJYY8rkqT", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_findelement.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d3a7e8ad009ce1cae84c86c52cdfc1b0857c4053", "parents": ["01aead8192bd5dca6f1dbef7424da9f0a70bc4a9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1283999 - Rename element retrieval tests to match spec; r=automatedtester a=test-only\n\nThe test_findelement.py name is misleading because it covers tests for\ncommands Find Element, Find Elements, Find Element From Element, Find\nElements From Element, and Get Active Element.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: J9UyDewDE7N", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_element_retrieval.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_findelement.py", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/unit-tests.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bf1de1c0467d9be21719126e40c819ce3a58cf75", "parents": ["d3a7e8ad009ce1cae84c86c52cdfc1b0857c4053"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1283999 - Run element retrieval tests on XHTML documents; r=automatedtester a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5dhnqsZhysn", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_element_retrieval.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "99ffd1a2577cc75f043dc6e17d21664088563d99", "parents": ["bf1de1c0467d9be21719126e40c819ce3a58cf75"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1283999 - Fix lookup of hyperlinks in XHTML documents; r=automatedtester a=test-only\n\nLower-case \"a\" matches hyperlinks in XHTML documents as well as HTML\ndocuments. Upper-case \"A\" only matches HTML documents.\n\nThe patch also refactors link text- and partial link text lookup into\ndistinct functions, so that there is no more worry about variable scoping\nin match blocks.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FB7MAmosBoR", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ce2cd885cd8c1830d362b1dc722f3a1154f5c327", "parents": ["99ffd1a2577cc75f043dc6e17d21664088563d99"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1283999 - Publish XPath find element functions; r=automatedtester a=test-only\n\nPublish the findByXPath and findAllByXPath functions to match the style\nof the recently introduces findByLinkText and findByPartialLinkText\nfunctions.\n\nDo note that this patch rearranges the input arguments these functions\ntake.  Possibly we do not have to send the root element as input at all.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4H7kpZBUsTw", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7e3531196e78da0229c241cc12d81cca24117120", "parents": ["ce2cd885cd8c1830d362b1dc722f3a1154f5c327"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Burns \u003cdburns@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285240: Trim leading and trailing space when finding elements by link text r=ato a=test-only\n\nThis gives up parity with the WebDriver project and brings us in line with the current\nspecification http://w3c.github.io/webdriver/webdriver-spec.html#dfn-link-text\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9OD6B2pKTfx", "files": ["testing/marionette/element.js", "testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_element_retrieval.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "874f9101c409c5cf62fc805a2cccf4b436a3c6c4", "parents": ["7e3531196e78da0229c241cc12d81cca24117120"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Burns \u003cdburns@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285240: Update tests to prevent redefinitions r=ato a=test-only\n\nThe tests had the same name which caused a redefinition meaning only one of the tests\nwas run.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LuflhcD4wKl", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette/tests/unit/test_element_retrieval.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3e019c07ecb8b1f1668d469e64eafa126bb72ceb", "parents": ["874f9101c409c5cf62fc805a2cccf4b436a3c6c4"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468414744, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "dburns@mozilla.com"}, "6207": {"changesets": [{"author": "Wes Kocher \u003cwkocher@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset 60a96ba61e4c (bug 1271899) for failures in browser_layout_editablemodel_bluronclick.js a=backout", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/inspector.xul", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser_layout_editablemodel.js", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser_layout_editablemodel_bluronclick.js", "devtools/client/themes/layout.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f8051a3ef4ec5842689306cc3d7b22a6ec439c9a", "parents": ["3e019c07ecb8b1f1668d469e64eafa126bb72ceb"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468448962, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kwierso@gmail.com"}, "6208": {"changesets": [{"author": "Eric Rahm \u003cerahm@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1236923 - Check int for overflow. r=peterv a=gchang", "files": ["parser/expat/lib/xmlparse.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "001086971e7b1f852d7ef524742de1359b14b172", "parents": ["f8051a3ef4ec5842689306cc3d7b22a6ec439c9a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nick Fitzgerald \u003cfitzgen@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1261869 - Fix leaks in devtools; r=ejpbruel a=gchang\n\nThere are two leaks addressed in this commit:\n\n1. The thread actor's `_debuggerSourcesSeen` set was never cleared. This set\nexists only as a performance optimization to speed up `_addSource` in cases\nwhere we've already added the source. Unfortunately, this set wasn't getting\ncleared when we cleared debuggees out and it ended up keeping the\n`Debugger.Source`, its referent, and transitively its referent's global alive. I\nfigured it was simpler to make it a `WeakSet` than to add it as a special case\nin `ThreadActor.prototype._clearDebuggees` and manage the lifetimes by hand. I\nthink this fits well with its intended use as an ephemeral performance\noptimization.\n\n2. Due to a logic error, we were not clearing debuggees in the memory actor's\n`Debugger` instance on navigations. This isn't really a \"proper\" leak, in that\nif you forced a GC, the old debuggees would go away as `Debugger` holds them\nweakly, however if there was no GC between navigations, then you could still see\nthe old windows (and everything they \"retained\") as roots in the snapshot. This\nissue is straightforward to fix once identified: ensure that `_clearDebuggees`\nis actually called on navigation.\n\nFinally, this commit adds a test that we don't leak Window objects when devtools\nare open and we keep refreshing a tab. When it fails, it prints out the leaking\nwindow's retaining paths.", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/test/shared-head.js", "devtools/client/memory/test/browser/browser.ini", "devtools/client/memory/test/browser/browser_memory_refresh_does_not_leak.js", "devtools/client/memory/test/browser/doc_empty.html", "devtools/server/actors/memory.js", "devtools/server/actors/script.js", "devtools/server/performance/memory.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a57ca21654194f5bc2af5916fa36abf5df057cb9", "parents": ["001086971e7b1f852d7ef524742de1359b14b172"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285974 - Land version 1.4.3 of the Loop system add-on in mozilla-central, rs=Standard8 for already reviewed code. a=lizzard", "files": ["browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/panels/js/roomViews.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/js/otSdkDriver.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/test/otSdkDriver_test.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/test/vendor/react-dom-server.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/vendor/react-dom-prod.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/vendor/react-dom.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/vendor/react-prod.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/vendor/react.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/content/shared/vendor/sdk.js", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ast/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/az/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/bg/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/bn-BD/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/bn-IN/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/bs/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ca/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/cs/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/cy/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/da/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/de/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/dsb/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/el/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/en-GB/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/en-US/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/eo/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/es-AR/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/es-CL/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/es-ES/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/es-MX/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/et/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/eu/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/fa/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ff/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/fi/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/fr/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/fy-NL/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/fy/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/gd/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/he/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/hi-IN/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/hsb/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/hu/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/hy-AM/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/id/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/it/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ja/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/kk/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/kn/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ko/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/lij/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/lt/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/lv/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ml/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/nb-NO/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/nl/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/nn-NO/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/pa-IN/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/pa/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/pl/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/pt-BR/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/pt-PT/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/rm/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ro/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ru/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/si/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/sk/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/sl/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/sq/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/sr/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/sv-SE/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/ta/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/te/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/th/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/tr/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/uk/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/zh-CN/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/chrome/locale/zh-TW/loop.properties", "browser/extensions/loop/install.rdf.in", "browser/extensions/loop/test/functional/loopTestDriver.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "564d7430ae0c2a79ee99e2d5d010a0ec8faf05db", "parents": ["a57ca21654194f5bc2af5916fa36abf5df057cb9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ting-Yu Lin \u003caethanyc@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285273 - Bail out early if ptFrame died in SelectWordOrShortcut(). r=masayuki a=gchang\n\nCheck ptFrame is still alive after calling\nChangeFocusToOrClearOldFocus() and IMEStateManager::NotifyIME().\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DtjoxtRIDdK", "files": ["layout/base/AccessibleCaretManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "84c59d136a9e54be69571b75a19e8a8ccff7b8a1", "parents": ["564d7430ae0c2a79ee99e2d5d010a0ec8faf05db"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468449985, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "kwierso@gmail.com"}, "6209": {"changesets": [{"author": "Edwin Flores \u003ceflores@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1264505 - Disable OES_EGL_image_external extension on Mali-400 MP - r=jgilbert, a=gchang", "files": ["gfx/gl/GLContext.cpp", "gfx/gl/GLContext.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "111933946ff48e5f10c96990e37fd91be8bfab32", "parents": ["84c59d136a9e54be69571b75a19e8a8ccff7b8a1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1276467 - Enforce that any items creating when we descend into an out-of-flow for which we don't have the proper clip are invisible. r=mattwoodrow, a=gchang\n\nJust giving them an empty visible rect isn't enough because the initial visible rect can be ignored when we compute visibility.\n\nWhen we enter an out of flow without saved clip data we set a flag on the builder indicating all items created should be invisible. When we enter a visible out of flow (ie one with saved clip data) inside the first out of flow we clear the flag so items created inside the second out of flow can be visible.", "files": ["layout/base/nsDisplayList.cpp", "layout/base/nsDisplayList.h", "layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e1a4db768898bffb040d7e86dd0283de33118ddc", "parents": ["111933946ff48e5f10c96990e37fd91be8bfab32"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Corey Ford \u003ccorey@coreyford.name\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1280344 - Use first continuation's normal position in computing sticky scroll ranges for APZ. r=dholbert, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: L0wRgCvb8h8", "files": ["layout/generic/StickyScrollContainer.cpp", "layout/reftests/position-sticky/inline-4-ref.html", "layout/reftests/position-sticky/inline-4.html", "layout/reftests/position-sticky/reftest.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f3a1bdbff211f14b6bff9fd143a230e8e6075c75", "parents": ["e1a4db768898bffb040d7e86dd0283de33118ddc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1284940 - Increase the max number of tiles in a TiledRegion. r=mstange, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4ndRuvllDAr", "files": ["gfx/src/TiledRegion.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b76b34484027e3673005bb3458fb9911d9e09b36", "parents": ["f3a1bdbff211f14b6bff9fd143a230e8e6075c75"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285409. Store out of flow data for frames we are going to descent into anyways (despite no intersection with the dirty rect) so we have the correct clip for them. r=mattwoodrow, a=gchang\n\nIf the frame already has the NS_FRAME_FORCE_DISPLAY_LIST_DESCEND_INTO bit we are going to descend into it anyways, so we may as well store the oof data so we can have the correct clip.\n\nSometimes we add the bit after this test though, so it doesn't allow us to have the proper clip in all cases.", "files": ["layout/base/nsDisplayList.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d661b598c1dbcbb7ed20494a5cba47d7c4aab8bd", "parents": ["b76b34484027e3673005bb3458fb9911d9e09b36"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Timothy Nikkel \u003ctnikkel@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1285411 - Mark preserve 3d children as \"force descend into\" before we mark absolute frames so that we can save the proper clip for more out of flow frames. r=mattwoodrow, a=gchang", "files": ["layout/generic/nsFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "73d312ee2d4e168ba49618dad6939629782f3c9c", "parents": ["d661b598c1dbcbb7ed20494a5cba47d7c4aab8bd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1286258 - Abort http channels that fail ContinueAsyncOpen() during service worker handling. r=valentin, a=gchang", "files": ["netwerk/protocol/http/HttpChannelChild.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ba3feb910fb31f5fb3df3528b2991b3a37b05cf", "parents": ["73d312ee2d4e168ba49618dad6939629782f3c9c"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468493189, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6210": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mike de Boer \u003cmdeboer@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1280294. r=MattN, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KdN5kETA9go", "files": ["toolkit/modules/sessionstore/XPathGenerator.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "781c5864339cee7aee9cac1f359b4cc3b4ed4cd5", "parents": ["2ba3feb910fb31f5fb3df3528b2991b3a37b05cf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrzej Hunt \u003cahunt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1278725 - Restore original \"up\" arrow scaling. r=liuche, a=gchang\n\nBefore introducing the folder count, the bookmark folder icon\nwas set as the drawable on a TextView. This actually resulted\nin scaling that doesn't preserve the aspect ratio. To reproduce\nthis in the new ImageView (added when we switched to a two-line\nfolder layout), we simply need to set the icon size explicitly\nand scale to fit the whole area (as opposed to setting two\nconstraints and fitting while preserving aspect ratio).\n\nThe folder/reading-list icons are unaffected as they already\nhave the expected aspect-ratio, the back-arrow is now scaled\nas expected.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Fl5JY3Lznau", "files": ["mobile/android/base/resources/layout/two_line_folder_row.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0f9e8e67acda1bdc44e161fc95e2a95c4c0030f2", "parents": ["781c5864339cee7aee9cac1f359b4cc3b4ed4cd5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Chen \u003cnchen@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1283739 - Prevent reentrant calls to showSoftInput and hideSoftInput; r=esawin, a=gchang\n\nAdd a check to showSoftInput and hideSoftInput To prevent an infinite\nrecursive loop of showSoftInput indirectly calling\nonCreateInputConnection, which calls showSoftInput again,", "files": ["mobile/android/base/java/org/mozilla/gecko/GeckoInputConnection.java"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "81f987b98a91032913ef201143e2e91db9b77bf7", "parents": ["0f9e8e67acda1bdc44e161fc95e2a95c4c0030f2"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468493366, "git_changesets": [null, null, null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6211": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1271899 - inspector box-model: add div wrapper to close editors on click;r=gl, a=gchang\n\nThe XUL tabpanel can no longer receive userfocus to avoid scrollbars\nstealing the focus. Editors are using the blur event to destroy\nthemselves, which was no longer working if a user click ended up on\nthe tabpanel element.\n\nAdd a wrapper inside the layout view panel taking\n100% width and height to make sure clicks performed outside of the layout\ncontainer will trigger a blur event on a focused editor.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JmZluQ6LzFl", "files": ["devtools/client/framework/test/shared-head.js", "devtools/client/inspector/inspector.xul", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser_layout_editablemodel.js", "devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser_layout_editablemodel_bluronclick.js", "devtools/client/themes/layout.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc7cc284b0c73491db3f45c165cf7ddb78fdde01", "parents": ["81f987b98a91032913ef201143e2e91db9b77bf7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468493455, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6212": {"changesets": [{"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1271899 - fix eslint error in browser_layout_editablemodel_bluronclick.js ;r=me, a=tomcat-bustage-fix\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: J6kDJyw8Kr7", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/layout/test/browser_layout_editablemodel_bluronclick.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "306382512096564f06aa175ddddeef59a90f36f0", "parents": ["fc7cc284b0c73491db3f45c165cf7ddb78fdde01"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468498151, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "cbook@mozilla.com"}, "6213": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jonathan Kew \u003cjkew@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1283573 - Don't attempt to look up a single-face-family name if the corresponding main family isn't available. r=mstange a=lizzard", "files": ["gfx/thebes/gfxMacPlatformFontList.mm", "modules/libpref/init/all.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0968b5fb96974b862d6901f9250644d8e478a30f", "parents": ["306382512096564f06aa175ddddeef59a90f36f0"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468514541, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jkew@mozilla.com"}, "6214": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jon Coppeard \u003cjcoppeard@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1282502 - Report an error if there are too many block scoped bindings r=shu a=abillings a=lizzard", "files": ["js/src/frontend/Parser.cpp", "js/src/jsscript.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "36faf180f49d6e6af84f55231052b1bac85b3bcd", "parents": ["0968b5fb96974b862d6901f9250644d8e478a30f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468516004, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jcoppeard@mozilla.com"}, "6215": {"changesets": [{"author": "Mike Conley \u003cmconley@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1284687 - Hide windows on shutdown while persisting session instead of closing them. r=billm a=lizzard\n\nWe were closing the windows before to improve perceived shutdown\nperformance, but we end up in a state where we're likely to miss\nout on the last ~2 seconds of session activity for most tabs per\nwindow. This is because we were removing the session update\nmessage listeners and resolving the flush Promises once the\ndomwindowclosed notification fired for the window.\n\nHiding the window allows us to wait for the messages properly.\n\nWhat's more, we weren't even collecting the window state after\nwe had flushed, so we have _always_ been missing (in the worst\ncase) about 2 seconds of session state per window. This addresses\nthat.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BEOIHV4EErf", "files": ["browser/components/sessionstore/SessionStore.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b4087792d5fa736a0dc18df7aeefecf0a34d99f", "parents": ["36faf180f49d6e6af84f55231052b1bac85b3bcd"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468518905, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "kwierso@gmail.com"}, "6216": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jared Wein \u003cjwein@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1270395 - Simplify the markup and padding rules for the UI Tour panel. r=Gijs, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GW5aht56XNv", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.xul", "browser/components/uitour/UITour.jsm", "browser/themes/shared/UITour.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8139a58cc0c18b47b6945f2a26fc347ef6f3a0b5", "parents": ["0b4087792d5fa736a0dc18df7aeefecf0a34d99f"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468519470, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "jwein@mozilla.com"}, "6217": {"changesets": [{"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1279208, fix rebase, r=me,a=me on a CLOSED TREE", "files": ["toolkit/components/places/AsyncFaviconHelpers.cpp", "toolkit/components/places/FaviconHelpers.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b9a4d34cb07363b0616321353610e47c1ddaa2ae", "parents": ["8139a58cc0c18b47b6945f2a26fc347ef6f3a0b5"], "tags": []}], "date": 1468602060, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "gijskruitbosch@gmail.com"}, "6218": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1284586 - Disable paint-skipping for scrollframes that we detect as having a CSS-clipped descendant. r=mstange, a=gchang\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AvjokFZMwdd", "files": ["layout/base/DisplayListCli